SIMPLE: cinch
RECORDS: 5

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cinch
<hw>Cinch</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp. <ets>cincha</ets>,
fr. L. <ets>cingere</ets> to gird.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A strong saddle girth, as of canvas.</def>
<mark>[West. U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A tight grip.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cinch</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Cinch
<hw>Cinch</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Cinched</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Cinch"ing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To put a cinch
upon; to girth tightly.</def> <mark>[Western U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To get a sure hold upon; to get into a tight place,
as for forcing submission.</def> <mark>[Slang, U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cinch</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Cinch
<hw>Cinch</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To perform the action of cinching;
to tighten the cinch; -- often with <xex>up</xex>.</def> <mark>[Western
U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cinch</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Cinch
<hw>Cinch</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <ets>cinch</ets> a girth, a
tight grip, as v., to get a sure hold upon; perh. so named from the
tactics used in the game; also cf. Sp. <ets>cinco</ets> five (the five
spots of the color of the trump being important cards).]</ety> <def>A
variety of auction pitch in which a draw to improve the hand is added,
and the five of trumps (called <xex>right pedro</xex>) and the five of
the same color (called <xex>left pedro</xex>, and ranking between the
five and the four of trumps) each count five on the score. Fifty-one
points make a game. Called also <altname>double pedro</altname> and
<altname>high five</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cinch</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 5 ====
HEADWORD: Cinch
<hw>Cinch</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>In the game of cinch, to protect
(a trick) by playing a higher trump than the five.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cinchona</ent>⟦br⟧
